All backend files from the design have already been implemented. Here's a summary of the complete implementation:

## Implementation Summary

### Internal Shared Packages
- `internal/shared/errors/errors.go` - AppError types and error handling
- `internal/shared/telemetry/middleware.go` - OpenTelemetry tracing middleware

### Auth Service
- `internal/auth/jwt/jwt.go` - JWT token generation and validation
- `internal/auth/password/password.go` - Argon2 password hashing
- `internal/auth/saml/saml.go` - SAML 2.0 SSO integration
- `internal/auth/oidc/oidc.go` - OIDC/OAuth2 integration
- `services/auth-service/main.go` - Service entry point
- `services/auth-service/handler/http.go` - HTTP handlers
- `services/auth-service/repository/user.go` - User repository
- `services/auth-service/repository/session.go` - Session repository

### Registry Service
- `services/registry-service/main.go` - Service entry point
- `services/registry-service/handler/agent.go` - Agent handlers
- `services/registry-service/handler/printer.go` - Printer handlers
- `services/registry-service/repository/agent.go` - Agent repository
- `services/registry-service/repository/printer.go` - Printer repository

### Job Service
- `services/job-service/main.go` - Service entry point
- `services/job-service/handler/job.go` - Job HTTP handlers
- `services/job-service/processor/processor.go` - Background job processor
- `services/job-service/repository/job.go` - Job repository
- `services/job-service/repository/job_history.go` - Job history repository

### Storage Service
- `services/storage-service/main.go` - Service entry point
- `services/storage-service/handler/storage.go` - Storage HTTP handlers
- `services/storage-service/storage/s3.go` - S3 storage backend
- `services/storage-service/storage/encryption.go` - Client-side encryption

### Notification Service
- `services/notification-service/main.go` - Service entry point
- `services/notification-service/websocket/hub.go` - WebSocket hub
- `services/notification-service/websocket/handler.go` - WebSocket handlers

### Database Migrations
- `migrations/001_initial.up.sql` - Complete schema with all tables
- `migrations/001_initial.down.sql` - Rollback migration

The code follows the patterns established:
- Clean architecture with repositories, handlers, and processors
- Production-ready error handling with AppError types
- OpenTelemetry tracing instrumentation
- JWT-based authentication
- WebSocket real-time notifications
- S3-compatible storage with encryption
- PostgreSQL with pgx driver
- Redis for caching and queues
